spec: agent-core.ai-docs/v1
namespace: "Domain\\Run"
fqcn: "Ineersa\\AgentCore\\Domain\\Run"
updatedAt: 2026-04-19
description: "Run lifecycle value objects — identity, state, status enum, and input DTO for starting runs."
files[5]{file,type,summary}:
  RunId.php,readonly final class,A value object representing a unique identifier for a run instance within the agent core domain. It encapsulates a string value to ensure type safety and immutability for run identification.
  RunHandle.php,readonly final class,A value object representing a specific run instance identified by a unique string ID. It serves as a lightweight carrier for the run identifier within the domain layer.
  StartRunInput.php,readonly final class,"This class serves as a value object for capturing the input parameters required to initiate an agent run. It encapsulates the system prompt, conversation history, optional run identifier, and associated metadata in a readonly structure."
  RunState.php,readonly final class,"Represents the immutable state of a run within the agent core domain, encapsulating identifiers, status, and sequence metadata. Designed as a value object to ensure consistent state representation across the application."
  RunStatus.php,enum,"Defines the discrete lifecycle states for an agent execution run, providing a type-safe representation of progress and completion. It serves as a value object to track the current status of a run within the domain model."